Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Peel and grate the @easy garlic{1/2%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Heat a glug of @olive oil{a glug} in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. When hot, add the mushrooms and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Fry until golden, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, fill a large #saucepan{} with the boiling water from the #kettle{} and pop onto high heat.

Add the @cavolo nero{100%g} and a pinch of salt to the pan of boiling water. Bring back to the boil and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @gnocchi{375%g}. Boil for ~{3%minutes}, then drain in a #colander{}.

Reduce the heat slightly and stir the garlic into the mushrooms. Cook for ~{1%minute}, stirring occasionally.

Stir the @creme fraiche{112.5%g} into the pan. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer untill thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Crumble in half the @goat's cheese{125%g}(). Stir to melt and remove from the heat. Mix in the parsley.

Add the drained gnocchi and cavolo nero to the sauce. Stir to coat the gnocchi. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it needs it.

Share between your bowls and crumble over the remaining goats cheese. DIG IN!